PMID- 501
TI  - [Case of small cell carcinoma of the bladder treated with adjuvant chemotherapy].
DP  - 2009
FAU - Okuda, Yasuo
TA  - Hinyokika kiyo
VI  - 55
PG  - 267-9
LID - 10.1/jp501 [doi]
AB  - A 72 year old man presented with macrohematuria and pollakisuria. Cystoscopy showed an abnormal mucosa on the right wall. Transurethral resection revealed small cell carcinoma of the bladder infiltrating adipose tissue. Adjuvant chemotherapy and radiotherapy were performed and follow up imaging showed disappearance of the tumor.

PMID- 502
TI  - Sarcopenia and postoperative outcomes after radical cystectomy
DP  - 2019
FAU - Rimar, Kalen
TA  - Urology
VI  - 60
PG  - 45-52
LID - 10.1/art502 [doi]
AB  - We evaluated the association between sarcopenia and postoperative outcomes after radical cystectomy in patients with muscle invasive bladder cancer. Skeletal muscle index was measured on computed tomography before surgery. Sarcopenia independently predicted complications and mortality in this retrospective cohort of consecutive patients treated at our institution.

